Japan â€™s government formed a team to
oversee decommissioning and water contamination measures at the
wrecked Fukushima nuclear power plant northeast of  Tokyo .  The group will be headed by Trade Minister Toshimitsu Motegi, METI official Tatsuya Shinkawa said at a briefing in
Tokyo today. Members of the team include Shunichi Tanaka,
chairman of the Nuclear Regulation Authority and vice ministers
of related ministries.  The measure is part of a push by Prime MinisterShinzo Abe
for the government to play a larger role in the cleanup at
Fukushima after the discovery of leaks at the site.  To contact the reporter on this story:
